  <title>GLib.string_new_len</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function string_new_len(init: String, len: Number(gssize)): <link xref="GLib.String">GLib.String</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_string_new_len()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Creates a new <link xref="GLib.String"/> with <code>len</code> bytes of the <code>init</code> buffer.
Because a length is provided, <code>init</code> need not be nul-terminated,
and can contain embedded nul bytes.</p>  <p>Since this function does not stop at nul bytes, it is the caller's
responsibility to ensure that <code>init</code> has at least <code>len</code> addressable
bytes.</p>

